data.enText: the language of ancient Rome and the official language of its empire

data.chText: 拉丁人（来自拉丁语系国家如西班牙、葡萄牙、意大利或法国）
data.enText: a person from countries where languages that have developed from Latin, such as Spanish, Portuguese, Italian or French, are spoken

data.chText: 拉丁音乐（源自拉丁美洲，节奏感强，适于跳舞）
data.enText: music of a kind that came originally from Latin America, typically with strong dance rhythms

data.chText: 拉丁语的；用拉丁语写成的
data.enText: of or in the Latin language

data.chText: 拉丁语系国家（或民族）的（如西班牙、葡萄牙、意大利或法国）；拉丁人的
data.enText: connected with or typical of the countries or peoples using languages developed from Latin, such as Spanish, Portuguese, Italian or French

means: 拉丁人(来自拉丁语系国家如西班牙、葡萄牙、意大利或法国)
拉丁音乐(源自拉丁美洲，节奏感强，适于跳舞)
拉丁语系国家(或民族)的(如西班牙、葡萄牙、意大利或法国)

value.def: Latin is the language which the ancient Romans used to speak.
Latin countries are countries where Spanish, or perhaps Portuguese, Italian, or French, is spoken. You can also use Latin to refer to things and people that come from these countries.

example.ex: Cuba was one of the least Catholic of the Latin countries...
example.tran: 古巴是拉丁语系国家中天主教化程度最小的国家之一。

example.ex: The enthusiasm for Latin music is worldwide.
example.tran: 全球掀起拉丁音乐热潮。

value.tran: （国家）操拉丁系语言的；拉丁语系国家的

value.def: Latins are people who come from countries where Spanish, or perhaps Portuguese, Italian, or French, are spoken or whose families come from one of these countries.

example.ex: They are role models for thousands of young Latins.
example.tran: 他们是千万拉丁青年的榜样。

trans: 拉丁情人(地中海地区或拉丁美洲男子，被视为有魅力的情人)
民间拉丁语(罗马帝国西部使用的拉丁口语)
